Program 5:
num = as.integer(readline("Enter the number "))
for(i in 1:10)
{
  print(paste(num,"x",i,"=",num*i))
}
----------------------------------------------------------------------
Output:
> num = as.integer(readline("Enter the number "))
Enter the number 10
> for(i in 1:10)
+ {
+   print(paste(num,"x",i,"=",num*i))
+ }
[1] "10 x 1 = 10"
[1] "10 x 2 = 20"
[1] "10 x 3 = 30"
[1] "10 x 4 = 40"
[1] "10 x 5 = 50"
[1] "10 x 6 = 60"
[1] "10 x 7 = 70"
[1] "10 x 8 = 80"
[1] "10 x 9 = 90"
[1] "10 x 10 = 100"
